          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833883?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：凯文·哈根/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>如果你想知道为什么现在放弃对抗通胀还为时过早，请查看劳工部周四发布的实际收入数据。经过两年生活水平下降后，美国人终于获得了加薪。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>美联储表示，7 月份消费者价格指数连续第二个月上涨 0.2%。过去 12 个月增长了 3.2%，远低于 2022 年 6 月 9.1% 的峰值。</p><p>过去 12 个月中，不包括食品和能源的所谓核心通胀上涨了 4.7%，服务业（扣除能源）上涨了 6.1%，因此价格之龙并未被消灭。 7 月下半月开始上涨的油价可能会导致 8 月通胀上升。但近几个月的趋势正在取得进展，其重要性在周四发布的实际平均每小时收入报告中得到了体现。</p><p> 7 月份扣除通货膨胀因素后的时薪上涨 0.3%，这是实际收入连续第五个月增长。由于前几个月通胀水平较高，今年实际时薪仅增长 1.1%。但随着通胀回到美联储 2% 的目标并且购买力下降，实际收入的趋势是正确的。附近的图表显示了拜登总统任期内的趋势，可以看到要弥补实际收入损失还有很长的路要走。</p><p>这些数字是抽象的，但对于家庭来说，它们是经济上是否成功的区别。它们是餐厅晚餐或家里的奶酪通心粉的区别。它们是一辆新车和保留行驶了 105,000 英里的旧车之间的区别。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833777?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>一些华尔街朋友认为美联储应该放松通胀，甚至有人认为美联储应该将通胀目标从2%提高到3%。彼得森研究所特别有力地提出了 3% 的目标，认为更高的目标将使美联储更灵活地保持较低的利率，从而保持较低的失业率。</p><p>我们不同意凯恩斯主义者仍然相信菲利普斯曲线在失业和通货膨胀之间进行权衡。通货紧缩可以与经济增长和低失业率共存——参见 20 世纪 80 年代。放弃 2% 的目标也会损害美联储对抗通胀的信誉。向市场传达的信息是，只要形势变得艰难，央行就会改变目标。如果经济陷入衰退，下一个目标会是4%吗？</p><p>伊丽莎白·沃伦（Elizabeth Warren）和唐纳德·特朗普（Donald Trump）等宽松货币政策的倡导者也有借口要求美联储在通胀水平较高的情况下降低利率。</p><p>美联储在下次公开市场委员会会议之前还有几周的时间，因此可以看看价格下跌趋势是否会持续。但价格稳定必须成为货币源泉，才能确保普通工人持续获得加薪。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 22:52:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-benefit-of-falling-inflation-43ecd77f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-benefit-of-falling-inflation-43ecd77f<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>通货膨胀</category><category>实际工资</category><category>美国联邦储备</category><category>美联储</category><category>杰罗姆·鲍威尔</category><category>拜登</category><category>经济学</category><category>消费者物价指数</category><category>价格</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>通货膨胀数字/价格指数</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>通货膨胀数字</category><category>价格指数</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden Walks a China Tech Tightrope]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>狭隘的投资禁令并不能消除商业风险。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590142260217187630"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590142260217187630"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 6:45 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-walks-a-china-tech-tightrope-52a40c74"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833869?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：FLORENCE LO/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>拜登总统周三发布的限制美国对中国军事技术投资的行政命令试图平衡国家安全和商业利益。问题在于北京没有区分两者，这就是中国商业风险不断上升的原因。</p><p>本周的行政命令是在政府先前对先进芯片和半导体制造设备出口限制的基础上发布的。白宫担心的是，共产党将把美国在人工智能等技术领域的风险投资和私募股权投资武器化。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>正如该命令所解释的那样，中国消除“民用和商业部门以及军事和国防工业部门之间的障碍，不仅通过研究和开发，而且还通过获取和转移世界尖端技术，以实现军事主导地位。”美国技术和管理人才的转让可以加速中国军事应用敏感技术的发展。</p><p>与此同时，该命令正确指出“开放的全球资本流动创造了宝贵的经济机会，并促进竞争力、创新和生产力。”鉴于中美经济的相互依存性，两国经济完全脱钩可能是不可能的，也不可取的。</p><p>因此，政府提出了“小院子、高围栏”的做法。该命令指示财政部长和商务部长禁止投资人工智能、量子计算和专为军事或情报用途设计的先进半导体。想想战斗无人机和破译密码的量子计算机。</p><p>但大多数先进技术可以服务于商业和军事双重目的。拜登的命令只要求美国公司向政府通报对具有双重用途能力的先进技术的投资，如果这些投资“可能对国家安全造成威胁”。这是一个很大的假设。</p><p>该命令不会像许多美国企业所担心的那样阻止大多数风险投资和私募股权投资。商业圆桌会议赞扬政府制定了“有针对性的机制来应对明显的国家安全风险”。它远远没有达到一些对华鹰派所敦促的全面投资限制。</p><p>汽车制造商仍将能够投资中国的自动驾驶系统。制药商可以与中国公司合作开发新药。这些狭窄的限制也向北京传达了美国希望缓和双边紧张局势的信息。</p><p>中国仍然猛烈抨击这些限制，但他们用自己的行为造成了这种情况。想想北京今年春天如何修改反间谍法，以针对共享“国家机密”的外国企业，“国家机密”的广义定义是可能损害其政治、经济、国防或外交利益的信息。</p><p>这意味着美国人可能仅仅因为提供咨询服务、从事学术研究或批评政权而受到起诉。贝恩公司四月份表示，中国当局对其在上海的员工进行了询问。中国警方还突击搜查了美国咨询公司凯盛投资集团的办公室。</p><p>中国正在惩罚美国芯片制造商，作为对政府出口管制的报复。北京最近以国家安全为由，阻止销售“关键基础设施”中的美光芯片。中国监管机构正在阻止英特尔收购以色列晶圆代工厂<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSEM" class="">Tower Semiconductor</a> <span class="company-name-type">。</span></p><p>中国正在发动无情的网络间谍活动，窃取西方知识产权并为网络攻击做准备。联邦调查局局长克里斯·雷（Chris Wray）表示：“我们看到中国正在寻找方法使其经济免受潜在制裁的影响，并试图在他们做出任何引起国际社会愤怒的事情时保护自己免受伤害。”</p>去年警告过。<p></p><h4> ***</h4><p>美国狭隘的投资禁令并不意味着美国企业可以放松警惕中国风险。入侵台湾将引发美国制裁并摧毁供应链。北京可能会没收美国商业资产。其经济影响将远远大于俄罗斯入侵乌克兰后发生的影响。</p><p>这就是为什么早在政府实施限制之前，企业就已经在中国“降低风险”。 2021年至2022年，美国对中国初创企业的投资下降了30%以上。2019年第一季度至今，美国对中国风险基金的投资下降了近80%。</p><p>由于经济放缓且产业政策未能带来更快的增长，中国需要更多的外国投资。拜登的命令在很大程度上不会阻止企业在中国投资，但他们可能会自行决定风险大于收益。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 22:45:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-walks-a-china-tech-tightrope-52a40c74</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-walks-a-china-tech-tightrope-52a40c74<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>中国</category><category>冷战</category><category>解耦</category><category>技术转让</category><category>知识产权盗窃</category><category>出口管制</category><category>双重用途</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>超级计算机</category><category>计算</category><category>电脑硬件</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>收购/合并/持股</category><category>收购/合并</category><category>企业行动</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>武器计划</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>收购</category><category>合并</category><category>持股</category><category>企业行动</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>武器计划</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>超级计算机</category><category>计算</category><category>电脑硬件</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Assassination in Ecuador]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>前记者、勇敢的总统候选人费尔南多·比亚维森西奥 (Fernando Villavicencio) 通过攻击“毒品政治”而树敌。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590142260811073280"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590142260811073280"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 6:42 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/assassination-in-ecuador-8694b109"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833863?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 8月9日，厄瓜多尔总统候选人费尔南多·维拉维森西奥在厄瓜多尔基多参加集会时挥舞着厄瓜多尔国旗。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：凯伦·托罗/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>拉丁美洲的政治动荡似乎离美国很远，但周三厄瓜多尔总统候选人费尔南多·比亚维森西奥遇刺事件是世界秩序日益混乱的一个迹象，也可能是美国对毒品需求的影响。</p><p>凶手身份尚未确定，但在这个曾经和平的国家，政治暴力不断增加。比亚维森西奥先生一直在开展一场无所畏惧的反对“毒品政治”的运动。他谴责“通过贩毒、非法采矿资助的犯罪经济”和“公共部门腐败的贿赂”。上周他收到了死亡威胁，但拒绝让步。 “我不害怕，”他说。</p><p>厄瓜多尔被跨国团伙占领，这些团伙争夺通往美国的贩毒路线的控制权。该国薄弱的机构无法与富有的墨西哥和阿尔巴尼亚黑手党相比。当法官、检察官和警察无法被收买时，谋杀也能发挥作用。比亚维森西奥的安全是如何崩溃的需要调查。但厄瓜多尔已成为杀戮场，2021 年至 2022 年间凶杀率几乎翻了一番。</p><p>在竞选国会议员之前，比亚维森西奥以挖掘政府腐败证据的记者而闻名。他的一些最有效的工作是国际性的。他的著作《厄瓜多尔中国制造》揭露了拉斐尔·科雷亚总统十年期间北京和基多之间的不正当交易。</p><p>比亚维森西奥不得不不止一次躲藏起来。当科雷亚因受贿罪被缺席判处八年监禁时，人们普遍认为比亚维森西奥将这位前总统绳之以法。在国会，他继续反对政府腐败。</p><p>美国为破案提供了帮助，比亚维森西奥也理应得到帮助。那些用自己的胃口和文化信号来满足毒品交易的美国人，也在整个美洲助长了谋杀和混乱。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 22:42:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/assassination-in-ecuador-8694b109</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/assassination-in-ecuador-8694b109<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>厄瓜多尔</category><category>比亚维森西奥</category><category>谋杀</category><category>总统</category><category>药物</category><category>阿尔巴尼亚黑手党</category><category>墨西哥</category><category>北京</category><category>受贿</category><category>中国</category><category>受贿</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>毒品贩运/交易</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩运/走私</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>腐败</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>贩毒</category><category>交易</category><category>金融犯罪</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩卖</category><category>走私</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Mike Pence’s Plan to Drill, Baby, Drill]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>这是共和党应该渴望在 2024 年与拜登进行的一场辩论。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11380450262913973852004590138542108044342"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11380450262913973852004590138542108044342"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/editorial-board" itemprop="url" rel="author">编委会</a></span>撰文</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 6:31 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/mike-pences-plan-to-drill-baby-drill-42ea0272"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832152?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">前副总统、共和党总统候选人迈克·彭斯</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：斯科特·摩根/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>前副总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/mike-pence">迈克·彭斯 (Mike Pence)</a>已获得 40,000 名捐款，并有资格参加 8 月 23 日的第一场共和党辩论，也许他会向密尔沃基的观众讲述他的新计划，宝贝，演习。彭斯周二发布了能源政策大纲，它既是标准的共和党一揽子计划，又提醒人们 2024 年的政治利害关系。</p><p>该计划称：“拜登政府领导下的民主能源政策建立在化石燃料不属于世界能源未来一部分的欺骗之上。” “根据能源部的数据，世界石油和天然气等液体燃料的消费量预计将从 2020 年的 9210 万桶/日增加到 2050 年的 1.259 亿桶/日，增长 36.7%。世界天然气的消费量预计将增长 36.7%。到 2050 年将增加 31.3%。”</p><p>指出拜登总统对绿色能源不切实际的假设是一个好的开始。彭斯先生承诺：</p><p> • “通过开放联邦土地出租来利用页岩革命。”</p><p> • 改革《国家环境政策法》，“将审批时间缩短一半，实现国内能源上网”。</p><p> • 审查并取消拜登先生的阻碍性行政命令，例如关于“碳的社会成本”的规定，“赋予联邦机构非凡的新权力来监管各种能源”。</p><p> • 废除“近年来实施的一系列炼油厂法规，并制定提高炼油厂产能的目标。”</p><p> • 放松对液化天然气基础设施的管制，以“建设更多的管道容量和出口终端设施”。</p><p> • 通过“依法保障能源开发和开采的机会，同时为政府租赁和批准制定具体时间表的法律”，提供长期监管的确定性，无论哪一方控制华盛顿。</p><p> • “取消司法部的‘环境司法办公室’，并停止帮助极端分子利用法院阻止国内能源生产的政策。”</p><p>这些想法使共和党人团结起来，但也让彭斯先生加入了政策辩论并把自己记录在案。美国人关心汽油和能源价格，因此如果共和党选民选择在这方面与拜登作斗争，那么这是有利的政治地形。提名前总统特朗普的风险在于，其他一切都将被关于他是否应该因试图推翻 2020 年选举而入狱或删除海湖庄园的安全磁带以隐藏文件的争论而淹没。</p><p>共和党人想在 2024 年 11 月讨论这个问题吗？或者他们是否想通过彭斯或新面孔向选民证明拜登试图抑制美国能源生产的做法是错误的？</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 22:31:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/mike-pences-plan-to-drill-baby-drill-42ea0272</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/mike-pences-plan-to-drill-baby-drill-42ea0272<author><![CDATA[The Editorial Board]]></author><category>活力</category><category>石油和天然气上游业务</category><category>采油</category><category>石油和天然气勘探</category><category>化石燃料</category><category>油和气</category><category>油</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>迈克·彭斯</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>活力</category><category>石油和天然气上游业务</category><category>采油</category><category>石油和天然气勘探</category><category>化石燃料</category><category>油和气</category><category>油</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Free Ron DeSantis]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>他在共和党初选辩论中需要的不是重置，而是回归他 2022 年 9 月的获胜信息。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590142672980221304"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590142672980221304"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/kimberley-a-strassel"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/B3-BS063_strass_AM_20180912122055.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/kimberley-a-strassel" itemprop="url" rel="author">金伯利·斯特拉塞尔 (Kimberley A. Strassel)</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 6:31 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/free-ron-desantis-florida-president-candidate-disney-debate-gov-fa0e36c"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833816?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">佛罗里达州州长罗恩·德桑蒂斯 7 月 28 日在爱荷华州得梅因发表讲话。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：sergio flores/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/ron-desantis">罗恩·德桑蒂斯</a>竞选活动继续重置。在某些时候，它可能会认为自己需要的不是重置，而是逆转——回到昔日的罗恩·德桑蒂斯。</p><p>去年九月，德桑蒂斯先生站在迈阿密附近的一个舞台上，发表了一场令人难忘的演讲。他热情地谈论了佛罗里达模式，巧妙地将其成功与自由市场保守主义哲学联系起来。该州蓬勃发展的经济是低税收、温和政府以及迅速放弃不科学的新冠封锁措施的产物。其盈余得益于财政审慎和扩大“经济蛋糕”的政策。广泛的择校导致考试成绩不断上升；公立大学的问责制使学费保持在较低水平。对执法的支持等于公共安全。</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>人们涌向佛罗里达州，因为“常识”和“理性”政策提供了更好的道路、值得信赖的选举和良好的就业机会。他对批判种族理论和性别意识形态的评论是在需要保护父母和雇员权利的更广泛背景下提出的。他利用<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/DIS" class="company-name">迪士尼</a>对“自由企业”和受补贴的“社团主义”做出了令人信服的区分。他用英语引用了罗纳德·里根最可怕的话：“我来自政府，我是来帮忙的”——尽管佛罗里达人呼吁更新这些话，以考虑到现代官僚国家。</p><p>罗恩·德桑蒂斯给人的印象是聪明、乐观、大胆，完全符合他经常提到的“普通”家庭的需求。六周后，这位佛罗里达州州长在连任选举中取得了压倒性的胜利，他赢得了农村选票、郊区选票、甚至城市选票，赢得了 67 个县中的 62 个县以及几乎所有人口群体的选票。正是这个公式使他成为唐纳德·特朗普连任的最大威胁。</p><p>罗恩·德桑蒂斯今天在哪里？被一堆民意调查数据、焦点小组和喋喋不休的顾问所窒息，这些都破坏了他之前的获胜秘诀。问题不在于竞选活动的策略、支出或资源部署的位置。问题在于州长采用了特朗普式的不满政治，这让他追逐了一部分无论如何也不会支持他的共和党初选选民。为此，他放弃了其他选民。</p><p>想想德桑蒂斯最近的经济演讲，这是重置的一部分。这是他不间断地谈论唤醒文化战争的一个值得欢迎的支点，其中埋藏着扎实的经济建议——正是推动佛罗里达发展的那种类型。并不是说你能找到它们，也不能听到佛罗里达州的成功故事。常识性的解释已经消失，被德桑蒂斯针对“中央计划者”、“统治阶级”、“精英”、“进步企业”、“根深蒂固的华盛顿政客”和“中国”的咆哮所排挤。这是一场旨在激怒人们、将选举简化为阶级和意识形态战争的演讲，或者正如德桑蒂斯先生总结的那样：“我们赢了。他们输了。”这与去年的罗恩·德桑蒂斯（Ron DeSantis）相差甚远，他去年成功地提出了经济增长惠及所有人的论点。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>了解更多波托马克手表</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-unprecedented-jack-smith-special-counsel-donald-trump-president-fraud-c076a2ee?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">史无前例的杰克·史密斯</a><span class="date">2023 年 8 月 3 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hunters-sweetheart-plea-deal-justice-department-lawyer-tax-gun-charge-whistleblower-irs-e271d08f?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">亨特甜心认罪协议</a><span class="date">2023 年 7 月 27 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/its-a-shame-about-wray-christopher-fbi-hearing-investigation-agents-washington-d54746d1?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">克里斯托弗·雷 (Christopher Wray) 真是太可惜了</a><span class="date">七月 13, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p>具有讽刺意味的是，德桑蒂斯去年在迈阿密的演讲是在全国保守主义会议上发表的，这是一个自称民粹主义者的知识分子聚会。他们希望共和党成为精简版伯尼·桑德斯，而且他们有明显的特朗普倾向。德桑蒂斯先生当时并不觉得有必要迎合他们，但现在似乎无法将他们从他的脑海中驱逐出去。这并不是说他的政策议程发生了变化，而是他将其硬塞进国家治理框架的努力混淆了他的信息，并把他送入了兔子洞和死胡同。看看他对乌克兰资金的转移和对冲，或者他浪费的时间抱怨迪士尼。</p><p>问题是为什么。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NYT" class="company-name">《纽约时报》</a> /锡耶纳最近的一项民意调查显示，特朗普在爱荷华州获得了 44% 的选票，不过其中 47% 的人表示他们愿意更换候选人。这意味着只有不到 25% 的爱荷华州选民忠诚于这位前总统——尽管他们肯定是忠诚的。全国民意调查显示出大致相同的动态。这些人最受煽动性政治的驱使，但他们最不可能认为有人会比特朗普做得更好。德桑蒂斯先生正在浪费时间。</p><p>他还失去了 70% 到 75% 的共和党初选选民，他们希望听到一位有想法、乐观和有计划的候选人。这些选民对能够展示保守派政策和选举胜利的可靠记录的竞争者持开放态度。他们不需要对特朗普进行全面的抨击，但不会介意偶尔的一瞥（德桑蒂斯的另一个失败策略）。他们不想要共和党版的伊丽莎白·沃伦（Elizabeth Warren），喋喋不休地谈论富人和“企业贪婪”。他们可能会欣赏那些不将世界分为“我们”和“他们”，而是宣扬美国广泛复兴信息的人。这有助于解释维韦克·拉马斯瓦米的崛起。</p><p></p><p>即使在重置之后，现在还不算太晚。德桑蒂斯先生在 8 月 23 日的共和党辩论中拥有绝佳的逆转机会——这是数百万美国人第一次真正关注候选人。让出现的人成为旧佛罗里达州州长。释放罗恩·德桑蒂斯。</p><p><em>写信给 kim@wsj.com。</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 22:31:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/free-ron-desantis-florida-president-candidate-disney-debate-gov-fa0e36c</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/free-ron-desantis-florida-president-candidate-disney-debate-gov-fa0e36c<author><![CDATA[Kimberley A. Strassel]]></author><category>保守主义</category><category>经济</category><category>纳特康</category><category>基本的</category><category>辩论</category><category>经济学</category><category>演讲</category><category>佛罗里达</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>罗恩·德桑蒂斯</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[John Paul II’s Legacy Lives On in World Youth Day]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>在里斯本，超过一百万人证明福音并没有浪费在年轻人身上。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590136394112656822"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590136394112656822"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">雷蒙德<span class="author" itemprop="name">·J·德·苏萨 (Raymond J. de Souza)</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 6:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/john-paul-iis-legacy-lives-on-in-lisbon-francis-world-youth-day-3d712998"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832760?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 1993 年 8 月 15 日，教皇约翰·保罗二世在科罗拉多州奥罗拉迎接世界青年日的参加者。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：杰夫·罗宾斯/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>三十年前的这个星期，一名在越南执行战斗任务的飞行员在丹佛努力控制他的直升机。当他将教皇约翰·保罗二世送到英里高体育场时，人群雷鸣般的欢呼声引起了骚动。飞行员带着一位和平朝圣者，但这次经历却奇怪地让他想起了战争。</p><p> 1993 年 8 月是世界青年日。那次大型会议改变了教皇和天主教会，恢复了年轻人的心可以被福音感动的信心。弗朗西斯教皇是一位非常不同的教皇，但他周日在里斯本举行了他的第四次聚会，有 150 万朝圣者参加，此前，里约热内卢（2013 年）、波兰克拉科夫（2016 年）和巴拿马城（2019 年）。他宣布，下一场将于 2027 年在首尔举行。</p><p> WYD 是约翰·保罗理解和激励年轻人的卓越能力的成果。他坚称“世界青年日不是任何人发明的；是年轻人自己创造了它们。” WYD 是教会日历的永久组成部分，也是地球上最大的宗教活动之一。以至于教皇本笃十六世在 2013 年退位后，他解释说，由于身体原因无法前往巴西，影响了他的决定。</p><p>为了庆祝 2000 年的伟大禧年，世界青年节在罗马举行。大约有两百万朝圣者前来参加闭幕式弥撒。开幕式上，几十万人挤进了圣彼得广场，涌入了周围的街道。我身边的一位加拿大记者同事顿时惊慌失措，寻找出路。她报道过几场战争，担心当大量年轻人挤满街道时，危险就在眼前。我告诉她这群人带着念珠，而不是枪。</p><p>上周在里斯本也是如此。欧洲再次陷入战争，教皇方济各与乌克兰朝圣者举行特别会议。 WYD 提供了反证，希望之军。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-832761?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 8月6日，教皇方济各在里斯本会见了数千名世界青年日志愿者。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：格雷戈里奥·博吉亚/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>WYD 始于 1984 年，当时约翰·保罗邀请年轻人到罗马与他一起参加棕枝主日的特别庆祝活动。组织者预计将有 60,000 人参加； 250,000 人这样做了。第二年他再次发出邀请。三十万人来了。约翰·保罗于 1986 年在罗马正式创立了世界青年日。 1987年，他在布宜诺斯艾利斯举办了第一届国际比赛。</p><p>丹佛是一个转折点。 1989年和1991年，世界青年节在圣地和朝圣地举行：西班牙圣地亚哥德孔波斯特拉和波兰琴斯托霍瓦。年轻人会来到丹佛这个没有特殊宗教意义的美国城市吗？美国主教对此表示怀疑，一些主教试图说服约翰·保罗放弃该计划。</p><p>他被平反了。毫不掩饰、充满信心地传播福音，可以吸引年轻人。今天的美国天主教领导层很大程度上是由 1993 年的丹佛塑造的。它重振了校园和年轻人的事工，甚至产生了一代“WYD 牧师”：在那里找到勇气接受他们呼召的年轻人。</p><p>我是他们中的一员。 1995 年，我参加了马尼拉世界青年节，估计有 500 万人参加了最后的弥撒。约翰·保罗传达了《约翰福音》的总主题：正如天父差遣了我，所以我也差遣了你们。我听到他对我说话。当还有很多人在路上时，发送起来会更容易。</p><p> 2002年，我在多伦多元旦节前几天在安大略省金斯顿受任命，这座大教堂里挤满了远至波兰和智利的朝圣者。</p><p>和我这一代的许多神父一样，世界青年节的经历让我相信天主教信仰能够对校园里的学生有吸引力，我后来在那里工作了 18 年。 20世纪50年代初，克拉科夫的年轻牧师约翰·保罗曾是共产主义下的大学牧师。半个世纪后，他学到的经验教训对自由世界具有重要意义。</p><p>里斯本是后基督教、甚至恐基督欧洲的一部分。世俗化的未来已经到来，教会已经失去了声音。在WYD，她再次找到了它。</p><p>弗朗西斯教皇不厌其烦地呼吁新的福音派能量，但有时他认为不能对年轻人抱有太多期望。在上周发表的一篇采访中，他赞扬了那些踢足球、养活穷人但远离教条、对贞洁视而不见的牧师。</p><p>约翰·保罗持不同的观点，总结了他在琴斯托霍瓦的做法：“你必须对自己要求很高，即使别人对你没有这样的要求。”</p><p>在周日的闭幕弥撒中，方济各教皇感到疲倦，只做了九分钟的备考讲道。但他知道年轻人有更多的期望，因此他在结尾时三重重复了约翰·保罗签名的圣经劝告：不要害怕！</p><p>约翰·保罗逝世十八年后，即丹佛事件三十年后，他的世界青年日仍然给教会带来了新鲜的活力——向年轻人展示基督教宣教的伟大冒险比世界上提供的上千种选择更好。</p><p><em>德苏扎神父是安大略省肯普特维尔的一名牧师，也是《国家邮报》和《国家天主教纪事报》的专栏作家。</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 22:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/john-paul-iis-legacy-lives-on-in-lisbon-francis-world-youth-day-3d712998</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/john-paul-iis-legacy-lives-on-in-lisbon-francis-world-youth-day-3d712998<category>天主教</category><category>维德</category><category>世界青年日</category><category>里斯本</category><category>丹佛</category><category>教皇</category><category>教会</category><category>弗朗西斯</category><category>罗马</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>宗教</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>约翰·保罗二世</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>宗教</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Books Resist Digital Domination]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>网上的干扰比比皆是，但阅读也有其自身的回报。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB10416900472008133444704589584843467799338"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB10416900472008133444704589584843467799338"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/brenda-cronin" itemprop="url" rel="author">布伦达·克罗宁</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 6:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/books-resist-digital-domination-streaming-adventures-time-attention-span-81b7fb16"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-805001?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：Getty Images/iStockphoto</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “现在还有人读书吗？”当我问一位朋友的下一本书进展如何时，她很想知道这一点。她不打算再写另一本书，她已经出版了 13 本非小说类畅销书。</p><p>在流媒体时代的网络干扰海啸中，她的问题并非毫无根据。然而，面对无穷无尽的播客、电影和连续剧，出版业的健康状况值得乐观。</p><p>在四月中旬的伦敦书展上，出版商们显得兴奋不已，而不是陷入困境。是的，对许多出版商来说是一笔财富的“流行病派对”已经结束了，哈珀柯林斯总裁布莱恩·穆雷（Brian Murray）告诉人群。但是，尽管人们不再被困在家里，有钱花，无处可去，但他们并没有放弃阅读，或者将他们的闲暇时间完全交给被动吸收在线内容。</p><p>阅读长篇小说或非小说作品（电子书、有声读物或纸质书）感觉更像是工作，而不是观看连续剧或听播客。这种努力得到了回报，将读者带入科马克·麦卡锡、马塞尔·普鲁斯特、希拉里·曼特尔等人创造的世界。</p><p>除了有声读物（显然很受欢迎）之外，阅读不太适合同时处理多项任务。相比之下，在跑腿时将注意力集中在播客上，或者在锻炼时在后台播放连续剧，因为知道自己可能会观看大约一半的节目，这是很容易的。</p><p>但一连串简单的替代方案并没有让我们读完。担心我们可能会陷入知识分子沙发土豆的境地，这并不是什么新鲜事。自从大约 80 年前电视机（后来被亲切地称为“白痴盒子”）闯入美国客厅以来，人们一直在为最低公分母和注意力持续时间的缩短而苦恼。但人们并没有停止读书，即使黑白逐渐发展为彩色和高清，频道激增，YouTube 也出现了。书籍经久不衰，不仅仅是因为拿着一本装订精美、散发着胶水和墨水味道的书，沉浸在其中所具有的无与伦比的吸引力。书籍改编自精装本和平装本。就像在线内容一样，它们无处不在——在手机、平板电脑和电脑上——而且它们的文字魅力并没有因为小屏幕而减弱。</p><p>可以肯定的是，流媒体是一个不可避免的竞争对手。医生的候诊室、机场、酒吧和其他公共场所都有刺眼的显示屏。漫步在几乎所有飞机的过道上，乘客托盘上的发光方块更有可能展示漫威电影宇宙的盛大场面，而不是《弗洛斯河上的磨坊》第 12 章。</p><p>阅读是一种承诺，正如我的作家朋友所证明的那样，写作更是如此。大多数写作都是孤独而艰苦的。但这两项努力都是值得的。与任何播客、电影或连续剧不同，书籍能带来红利——由文字构建的令人难忘的人物和场景。</p><p>当然，生活中还有“伟大的英国烘焙秀”和“卡拉马佐夫兄弟”的空间。这只是时间问题。</p><p><em>克罗宁女士是该杂志的编辑特稿副编辑。</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 22:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/books-resist-digital-domination-streaming-adventures-time-attention-span-81b7fb16</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/books-resist-digital-domination-streaming-adventures-time-attention-span-81b7fb16<author><![CDATA[Brenda Cronin]]></author><category>阅读</category><category>书展</category><category>伦敦</category><category>流媒体</category><category>电视</category><category>白痴盒子</category><category>注意力持续时间</category><category>大流行</category><category>图书</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>电影</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>图书</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>电影</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘The Country of the Blind’ Review: Journey Into Darkness]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>对于许多盲人来说，视力的丧失既不是立即的，也不是完全的。失明既是一种身体状况，也是一种精神状态。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590137141057854382"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833374?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">照片：盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11667163785710763363504590137141057854382"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"><span class="author" itemprop="name">尚克莱尔</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 6:29 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-country-of-the-blind-review-journey-into-darkness-86d1734f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>在 HG 威尔斯 (HG Wells) 1904 年的短篇小说《盲人之国》中，一位探险家跌入了一个偏远的山谷，这里曾经是 15 代盲人居民的家园。他们如此彻底和满足地适应了失明，以至于他们无法想象视力意味着什么。安德鲁·利兰（Andrew Leland）借用了这个故事的标题来写他关于患有退行性眼病的引人入胜的回忆录。 “与威尔斯饰演的角色不同，他最终逃脱了，”他写道，“我会留下来，慢慢成为一名入籍公民。” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/schemas/1b61d1b7-b505-4850-a244-e5cab8734808.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>现年 42 岁的 Leland 先生在大学一年级时被诊断出患有色素性视网膜炎。 RP 是一种无法治愈的遗传性眼病，通常在青少年时期以夜盲症的形式出现。周边视力日益受限意味着大多数 RP 患者到中年时就已经失明。但这种情况值得注意的是它的渐进性：不存在“失明”的决定性时刻，只是“失明”的持续过程。 Leland 先生仅保留了 6% 的视野，并且不知道他的残余中心视力还能保留多久。</p><p>正如利兰先生指出的那样，失明往往是一种介于两者之间的情况。只有15%的盲人完全没有光感。对于大多数视力不同程度的盲人来说，认为自己是盲人的原因与心理变化和身体变化一样多——在某些时候，利兰先生不得不认定自己是盲人。他现在认为失明既不是“生物学事实”也不是“社会建构”，而是“介于这两个极端之间”。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="713" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833381?width=639&amp;height=713" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">安德鲁·利兰</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：格雷戈里·哈尔彭</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>在《盲人的国度》的 10 个章节中，作家兼播客制作人将自己的个人经历融入了失明文化史中，涉及的主题包括男子气概、种族、宗教、艺术和残疾人权利运动。他告诉读者，为了研究这本书，他想去“失明与当代生活交叉的地方”。尽管如此，他的叙述中最令人难忘的部分还是纯粹自传的亲密时刻。</p><p>例如，当他第一次在公共场合使用手杖时，是在一个酒吧狂欢的夜晚，有黑暗和醉酒的双重保护。他形容拿着它“就像一支巨大的钢笔，在人行道上涂鸦”。读者们还了解许多其他的生活事件：通过了使他符合法定失明资格的测试；颤抖着剪断儿子的脐带，担心他会错过目标；了解哪种基因突变导致了他的 RP。他在 30 岁出头就不再开车了，几年后也不再阅读印刷书籍。他写道，这种新生活有时感觉就像“一次漫长的故障排除过程”。经过两年辛苦学习盲文后，他尝试给热情的一年级学生读一本盲文图画书。他们在睡前没有读完这本书。</p><p>在这种情况下，就像在其他情况下一样，利兰先生提供了自己的经验，作为盲人和视力正常世界之间的桥梁。他指出，旨在增加盲人接触文学的机会的“有声书籍”自 20 世纪 30 年代中期以来就已存在。 90 年代初的盲人技术专家首先开发了 EPUB，现在已成为一种广泛使用的电子书格式。不过，尚不清楚盲人的虚拟可供性世界是否会立即改善他们的生活。</p><p>作者指出，随着屏幕阅读的出现，学习盲文的盲人越来越少。许多“盲文传播者”——包括一些盲人专业人士——警告说，今天的学生“从技术意义上来说是文盲”。在这场辩论的表面之下，隐藏着一个关于教育差异的令人不安的事实：超过五分之一的有视力障碍的美国人没有完成高中学业，是视力正常的美国人的两倍，利兰先生认识到，盲人失业率70% 的人表示，“在盲人中，从事全职工作，无论什么工作，都是少数。”他想知道，随着他的视野受到侵蚀，他作为一名记者的日常工作会发生怎样的变化。</p><p>利兰先生写道，失明是“一个人生命中的中心和偶然”。他仍然可以独立步行导航——他只需考虑他以前从未考虑过的因素。他还是失明前的那个人，但现在已经不是了。他认为，在生活的各个方面，“我们都生活在这种模糊性之中”，但信息量有点少。他表示，他的失明并不意味着他完全丧失视力，这可以比作离婚，但离婚并没有完全切断前任之间的联系。在其他地方，他将残疾比作不情愿地加入俱乐部。接下来，同样的缩小：“但这也是当代生活的一个基本特征：你可能不喜欢你的家庭，但那是你不能离开的另一个俱乐部。”当这本书不觉得有必要普及，而是与利兰先生的失明之旅保持一致时，它是最好的。</p><p>在《盲人的国度》的结尾处，利兰先生已经克服了之前推迟收养手杖的羞耻感。但随着手杖成为他日常生活的一部分，他也更加意识到人们对无处不在的失明信号的反应：行人穿过马路的另一边，父母“在我还半岁的时候就把孩子拉到一边”。挡开。”对于利兰先生来说，每个陌生人都成为潜在的对手，能够使他陷入社会孤立。 “这不是穿越世界的方式，”他意识到。现在，他拄着拐杖，脸上挂着“半微笑”，对于那些不可避免地观看的陌生人来说，这让他显得平易近人。更重要的是，当他在世界各地行走时，控制自己的形象会提醒他对他人和自己要有耐心：“我恢复到一个人与另一个人相遇的状态，‘平静而友善’。”借用书中的一句话，他学会了优雅地失败——这一教训因其特殊性，不禁引起更广泛的共鸣。</p><p><em>尚女士是《华尔街日报》的罗伯特·L·巴特利研究员。</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 22:29:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-country-of-the-blind-review-journey-into-darkness-86d1734f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-country-of-the-blind-review-journey-into-darkness-86d1734f<category>眼睛状况</category><category>图书</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>眼睛状况</category><category>图书</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘King Coal’ Review: Mining for Stories in Appalachia]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Elaine McMillion Sheldon writes, directs and narrates a documentary film about the cultural hold of coal in West Virginia, part of so many families&#39; histories, including her own <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590138290968128082"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833830?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Gabby Wilson and Lanie Marsh in &#39;King Coal&#39;</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Curren Sheldon </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590138290968128082"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Kyle Smith</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 10, 2023 5:43 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/king-coal-review-documentary-mining-for-stories-in-appalachia-fbefbf36"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> There are fewer than 12,000 coal miners left in West Virginia, but the combination of the value, power and danger of the rock in question means the job retains a mythic quality. Filmmaker Elaine McMillion Sheldon, a native of the state, has done a breathtakingly expressive job of capturing the strangeness, the beauty and the devastation of her homeland in the poetic, entrancing documentary “King Coal.”</p><p> Framed in part as the unvarnished viewpoint of two aspiring, unidentified teen dancers, girls who are filmed cinema verité-style as they go about ordinary tasks, the film was shot in the coal-producing states where soot-faced miners turn up in fourth-grade classrooms to talk about the experience of nearly getting killed in an explosion of methane gas and where young beauties compete in the Bituminous Coal Queen Pageant. (In an amusing tangent, while working on a school project the two girls who roam the perimeter of the film use software to try to figure out how to pronounce “bituminous.”) High-school football players—the Miners, from Matewan, W.Va.—pause in the process of rushing onto the field to touch what they treat like a holy lump of coal from the mountain that was torn away to create the gridiron. In these parts, people are grateful for coal even as they hold memorial services for those sacrificed in the hunt for it. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> More Film Reviews</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gran-turismo-review-orlando-bloom-david-habour-sony-playstation-4e17f79d?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Gran Turismo&#39; Review: From Game Controller to Steering Wheel</a> <span class="date">August 10, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-best-biopics-of-the-21st-century-oppenheimer-ef971e66?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">The Best Biopics of the 21st Century—So Far</a> <span class="date">August 8, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/dreamin-wild-review-casey-affleck-zooey-deschanel-walton-goggins-227d1130?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Dreamin&#39; Wild&#39; Review: When Past Melodies Resurface</a> <span class="date">August 3, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-mutant-mayhem-review-coming-out-of-their-shells-again-f90305db?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Mutant Mayhem&#39; Review: Coming Out of Their Shells Again</a> <span class="date">August 2, 2023</span></li></ul></div></div><p> Ms. Sheldon, who wrote and directed the film and provides its quietly enchanting voiceover narration, largely overlooks the political and economic questions attaching to the coal industry in favor of considering its cultural footprint in Appalachia. On the evidence provided here, coal continues to have a staggering hold over the regional collective imagination. Ms. Sheldon&#39;s great-grandfather, grandfather, father and brother have all been miners. Her brother compares the experience of traveling into the core of the mountain to visiting outer space, and though the film is too short on footage of actual mining, the few minutes of images we do see clarify that on its best day, the experience is an alarming one. The worst days are ones we&#39;d rather not think about as we flip the light switch. Coal still supplies more than 10% of US energy, and in previous generations it was by far the leading source of electricity in the country. But the human toll is evident. One victim of a methane blast, we learn, was discovered with his glasses fused to his face by the heat. Ms. Sheldon&#39;s grandfather used to work in the mines all day, then dig graves afterward.</p><p> Ms. Sheldon, who received an Oscar nomination for her 2017 documentary short about opioids, “Heroin(e),” believes that coal is both dead and alive—a sort of ghost that haunts the mountains and all who dwell among them. Combined with a superb musical score by Bobak Lotfipour and exquisitely composed images shot by Sheldon&#39;s husband, cinematographer Curren Sheldon, the conceit makes for an appropriately grave and spectral experience.</p><p> I&#39;m not sure the two girls ( Gabby Wilson and Lanie Marsh, neither of whom is provided with much fleshing out) add much to the film—they seem to be intended as symbols of a coal-free future, but aren&#39;t as compelling as the footage of odd rituals, gorgeous countryside and somber reflections. Their scenes, which were unscripted, do take us to some unexpected places, however. We meet one girl&#39;s grandmother and she tells an agonizing story about how a family member was injured so badly by falling slate that he had to retire, six months shy of the point at which he would have qualified for a pension.</p><p> Vast wealth may be associated with coal, but hardly any of it seems to reach the people who dig it up. “King Coal” is less a howl of injustice, however, than it is a reverie for a time that is quickly passing. The places coal built will change too, and so a tinge of sadness for bygone ways envelops the film. We are in “the frail days of our king,” Ms. Sheldon says, but she notes that “our soot-covered lives can be beautiful.” The post-coal era can&#39;t come fast enough for some. For others, coal is at the heart of who they are and where they came from. “Some think place matters less today,” the filmmaker notes. Her lovely, lyrical film makes a profound statement against that notion.</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 21:43:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/king-coal-review-documentary-mining-for-stories-in-appalachia-fbefbf36</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/king-coal-review-documentary-mining-for-stories-in-appalachia-fbefbf36<category>艺术评论</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>电影</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>艺术回顾</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>电影</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Telemarketers’ Review: Phony Phone Calls]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> A three-part HBO docuseries follows the years-long whistleblowing journey of two scrappy employees at Civic Development Group, which misrepresented charities and was fined $18.8 million in 2010 after a federal investigation <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590140392024492612"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830603?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Sam Lipman-Stern</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: HBO </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590140392024492612"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"><span class="author" itemprop="name">约翰·安德森</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">Aug. 10, 2023 5:41 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/telemarketers-review-phony-phone-calls-hbo-29d70f21"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Journalism has been called history in a hurry; documentaries have been called news in slow motion. But some other shorthand has to be invented for “Telemarketers,” in which a pair of uncredentialed but impassioned citizen investigators tell a story that spans nearly 20 years, creating a scroungy, antic masterpiece in the process. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4></h4><p> <strong>Telemarketers</strong></p><p> <em>Begins Sunday, 10 pm, HBO</em></p></div></div><p> Directed by Adam Bhala Lough and Sam Lipman-Stern, the three-part series (executive producers include Danny McBride, David Gordon Green, Josh Safdie and Benny Safdie ) is based largely on footage Mr. Lipman-Stern and others collected during the seven years he was an employee of Civic Development Group. What did a CDG job involve? “We call people up on behalf of some b— organizations and chisel &#39;em out of money,” says Patrick J. Pespas, who is high at the time, and will get higher later. But despite his very apparent addiction problems, he is one of the more memorable subjects ever to inhabit a documentary, period. He&#39;s Mr. Lipman-Stern&#39;s secret weapon, and as the director says a “born whistleblower,” who rises out of the ashes of his abuse problems because he has found a cause, and a collaborator.</p><p> Both men express their lingering indignation for the New Jersey-based CDG, which the Federal Trade Commission began investigating in the late &#39;90s. In 2010, the company was fined a then-record $18.8 million to settle charges that it misled consumers into believing “they were donating directly to legitimate charities serving police, firefighters, and veterans, when in fact only a small slice of the donations actually went to these charities,” as the FTC website explains it. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830604?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Patrick Pespas</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: HBO </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>更多电视评论</h4><p></p><ul class="articleList"><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/red-white-royal-blue-review-prime-video-uma-thurman-nicholas-galitzine-taylor-zakhar-perez-67a80cb8?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Red, White &amp; Royal Blue&#39; Review: Intimate International Relations</a> <span class="date">August 10, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/strange-planet-review-alien-characters-human-world-nathan-pyle-dan-harmon-apple-tv-586b1510?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">&#39;Strange Planet&#39; Review: Alien Characters, Human World</a> <span class="date">August 8, 2023</span></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-lost-flowers-of-alice-hart-review-thorny-drama-on-the-australian-prairie-781af5e8?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">《爱丽丝·哈特的失落之花》评论：澳大利亚大草原上的棘手戏剧</a><span class="date">2023 年 8 月 3 日</span></li><li><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-wild-sides-review-survival-of-the-fiercest-a683a104?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_self" class="icon none">《The Wild Sides》评论：最激烈的生存</a><span class="date">2023 年 8 月 3 日</span></li></ul></div></div><p>Messrs. Lipman-Stern and Pespas had been there for years at that point, working the phones, conning the rubes, doing the drugs and helping turn the workplace into a kind of frat house for what one character calls “a bunch of criminals”—past, present and on probation. As one veteran CDG telemarketer, Larry Lazare, observes, “CDG provides a public service almost by accident—by providing jobs to people who are unemployable.” People with criminal records, in other words, whose job involved raising money for law enforcement. And whose probation officers would be informed if an employee underperformed and was fired.</p><p> The filmmakers got very little cooperation from their secondary target, the Fraternal Order of Police, a nationwide organization whose various lodges were clients of CDG; some FOP officials who offer to do interviews back out at the last minute. Some of the more legitimate interviewees who are on camera— David Vladeck, the former director of the FTC&#39;s Bureau of Consumer Protection; Ann Ravel, onetime member of the Federal Election Commission; veteran consumer reporter Sarah Kleiner —are frank about the slim chances of implicating any police organization in telemarketing scams past or present, though they admire the efforts being made by the team of Lipman-Stern and Pespas, who are short on journalistic credentials but long on nerve. They are dogged when others would have turned tail. They even get a face-to-face meeting with Sen. Richard Blumenthal of Connecticut, who promises action, but can&#39;t get out of the room fast enough. At least he showed up.</p><p> Mr. Lipman-Stern (with his cousin, Mr. Lough, mapping the investigative trail) wants to make a film. So does the very entertaining, damaged but charming Mr. Pespas. But the latter is also after something else, and as much as “Telemarketers” is a takedown of those people who ruin your dinner with their phone calls and con old people “out of their cigarette money,” it is also a testament to the human spirit—exactly the kind of cloying sentiment at which Mr. Pespas would likely laugh out loud.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> -先生。安德森是《华尔街日报》的电视评论家。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 21:41:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/telemarketers-review-phony-phone-calls-hbo-29d70f21</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/telemarketers-review-phony-phone-calls-hbo-29d70f21<category>艺术评论</category><category>Audiovisual Production</category><category> Television Program Production</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>企业社会责任</category><category>Environmental/Social/Governance</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Charities/Volunteering</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>艺术回顾</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>corporate social responsibility</category><category> environmental</category><category> social</category><category> governance</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>charities</category><category> volunteering</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>audiovisual production</category><category> television program production</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden’s IRS Chases Chump Change]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> The amount of improper pandemic payments dwarfs what its new agents stand to recoup for taxpayers. <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB11380450262913973852004590138012048123640"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB11380450262913973852004590138012048123640"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name">Phil Gramm</span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name">Jodey Arrington</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 10, 2023 5:37 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-irs-chases-chump-change-food-stamps-enforcement-fraud-pandemic-9217ee2"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="607" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833221?width=860&amp;height=607" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit"> Illustration: Chad Crowe</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Criminals stole at least $1 trillion from taxpayers during the pandemic. To date the Biden administration has offered only lip service and modest funding to try to reclaim these funds and punish wrongdoers. Meanwhile President Biden is hiring an army of Internal Revenue Service agents to shake down Americans he claims are tax avoiders. And his commitment is concrete—$80 billion to hire 87,000 new IRS agents. According to Congressional Budget Office estimates, all that extra manpower and money will net the federal government only about $100 billion. Why not spend some of it settling a far larger bill?</p><p> The Government Accountability Office estimates the federal government made $528 billion in improper payments in 2021 and 2022. Some were the result of honest mistakes. But many swindlers saw opportunity in the blizzard of pandemic relief programs, filing false claims and outright stealing taxpayer money. As astonishing as half a trillion dollars in estimated improper payments is, the real cost of the unprecedented mismanagement and fraud is much higher. GAO numbers exclude improper payments in major programs like Pandemic Unemployment Assistance and food stamps because the federal agencies running those programs didn&#39;t bother reporting them, despite being required to do so by law.</p><p> The House Ways and Means Committee estimates that fraudulent payments made under the Pandemic Unemployment Assistance program alone could be as high as $400 billion, only $5 billion of which has been recovered. Almost all the crooks who stole taxpayer money are getting away with it. Likewise, President Biden has failed to hold any of his appointees accountable for the massive amounts of money stolen under their noses. Julie Su, who ran the Pandemic Unemployment Assistance at the Labor Department, has been offered a promotion. Mr. Biden has nominated her to be labor secretary.</p><p> With the massive expansion in food stamps during the pandemic, the level of fraudulent payments mushroomed. Estimated overpayment rates rose from the prepandemic average of 4.2% to 9.8% in 2022. The actual fraud rate is worse, since the food-stamp program doesn&#39;t count overpayments of up to $48 a month as improper payments.</p><p> Last year a Democratic Congress provided the administration with $80 billion of guaranteed funding over 10 years for the IRS. But in 2021 that same Congress provided only $2 billion to deal with fraud in pandemic-era programs—and the administration didn&#39;t use most of it. More than two years later, $1.6 billion of those unspent funds have finally been made available to the states to prevent fraud and “promote equitable access and ensure the timely payment of benefits.” The Biden administration in 2024 is asking for only another $1.6 billion to address the massive level of pandemic fraud.</p><p> Note that in 2022 alone the IRS itself made an estimated $25.4 billion in improper payments in only three programs: earned-income tax credits, additional child tax credits and American opportunity tax credits. The GAO estimates that the level of improper payments by the IRS in these programs runs as high as 28% of all payments made. Yet none of the $80 billion in new IRS funding is specifically earmarked to deal with fraud in the welfare programs funded with tax credits and administered by the IRS.</p><p> Despite the administration&#39;s claim, the new IRS enforcement revenues flowing from its $80 billion surge in funding will come primarily from middle and upper-middle income Americans. The Joint Committee on Taxation <a href="https://www.finance.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/irs_enforcement_jct_analysis.pdf" target="_blank" class="icon none">estimates</a> that 78% to 90% of the money extracted from underreported income would come from those making less than $200,000 a year. Only 4% to 9% would come from those making more than $500,000 a year.</p><p> A Senate Finance Committee <a href="https://www.finance.senate.gov/ranking-members-news/myth-vs-fact-tax-title-of-the-inflation-reduction-act-of-2022" target="_blank" class="icon none">analysis</a> shows the new IRS enforcement spending would “predominantly hit taxpayers who have low (or very low) Adjusted Gross Income.” Nearly half of the audits would hit Americans making $75,000 a year or less.</p><p> It is time for Congress to correct the Biden administration&#39;s misplaced priorities. Rather than spending $80 billion targeting taxpayers, use some of that money to go after those who cheated taxpayers and abused programs aimed at helping needy people during a health emergency. Hunt down swindlers, recoup fraudulent payments, hold criminals accountable, and put in place safeguards such as an identity and eligibility verification system. This would be fair to taxpayers and deter future fraudulent claims for federal benefits.</p><p> Congress has a choice: Harass taxpayers or track down the crooks who stole their money.</p><p> <em>Mr. Gramm, a former chairman of the Senate Banking Committee, is a visiting scholar at the American Enterprise Institute. Mr. Arrington, a Texas Republican, is chairman of the House Budget Committee. Steve McMillin contributed to the article.</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 21:37:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-irs-chases-chump-change-food-stamps-enforcement-fraud-pandemic-9217ee2</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/bidens-irs-chases-chump-change-food-stamps-enforcement-fraud-pandemic-9217ee2<category> pandemic payments</category><category> irs</category><category> taxpayers</category><category>欺诈罪</category><category>criminals</category><category> improper payments</category><category> food stamps</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算/税收</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>Financial Crime</category><category>欺诈罪</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>Welfare/Benefit Fraud</category><category> Welfare/Social Services</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论/意见</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算</category><category>税收</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>financial crime</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>welfare</category><category> benefit fraud</category><category> social services</category><category>内容类型</category><category>评论</category><category>意见</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>观点</category></item></channel></rss>